cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper deals with privacy-preserving data collection and analysis, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of computer security (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and information theory (cs.IT). The paper specifically focuses on local differential privacy, which is a technique used to protect the privacy of individual users while still allowing for statistical analysis of their data. Therefore, cs.CR and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.DS, and cs.IT.
